        \frac{n_1\Exp{1 - e^{-\lambda C_i}}{C_i} + n_2\Exp{1 - e^{-\lambda e^\beta C_i}}{C_i}}{\lambda^2} & \frac{1}{\lambda} n_2\Exp{1 - e^{-\lambda e^\beta C_i}}{C_i} \\
        \frac{1}{\lambda} n_2\Exp{1 - e^{-\lambda e^\beta C_i}}{C_i} & n_2\Exp{1 - e^{-\lambda e^\beta C_i}}{C_i}
    \end{bmatrix}
\end{align}\] Let \(\Exp{r_{i1}} = \Exp{1 - e^{-\lambda C_i}}{C_i}\) and \(\Exp{r_{i2}} = \Exp{1 - e^{-\lambda e^\beta C_i}}{C_i}\). We know the asymptotic variance of the MLE is the inverse of the Fisher information matrix. The inverse is: \[\begin{align}
    \frac{\lambda^2}{n_{1} n_{2} \Exp{r_{i1}}\Exp{r_{i2}}}
    \begin{bmatrix}
      n_2 \Exp{r_{i2}}  & -n_2\Exp{r_{i2}}/\lambda \\
        -n_2\Exp{r_{i2}}/\lambda & \frac{n_1\Exp{r_{i1}} + n_2\Exp{r_{i2}}}{\lambda^2}
    \end{bmatrix} =
    \begin{bmatrix}
      \frac{\lambda^2}{n_1\Exp{r_{i1}}}  & -\frac{\lambda}{n_1 \Exp{r_{i1}}} \\
       -\frac{\lambda}{n_1 \Exp{r_{i1}}} &
\frac{n_1\Exp{r_{i1}} + n_2\Exp{r_{i2}}}{n_1 n_2 \Exp{r_{i1}}\Exp{r_{i2}}}
    \end{bmatrix}
\end{align}\] So the asymptotic standard error for \(\beta\) is \[\sqrt{\frac{n_1\Exp{1 - e^{-\lambda C_i}}{C_i} + n_2\Exp{1 - e^{-\lambda e^\beta C_i}}{C_i}}{n_1 n_2\Exp{1 - e^{-\lambda C_i}}{C_i}\Exp{1 - e^{-\lambda e^\beta C_i}}{C_i}}}\]

